content.problemStatement:
Unary operators perform operations on a single variable or operand to produce a new value.

Examples as follows
1. Unary minus
```cpp
int x = 5;
int y = -x;  // Sets the value of y as -5
```
2. Increment
```cpp
int x = 1;
int y = ++x;  // Prefix increment first convers x = 2 and then sets y = x
int z = x++;  // Suffix or postfix increment first sets z = x = 2 and then x changes to 3
```
3. Decrement
```cpp
int x = 4;
int y = --x;  // Prefix increment first converts x = 3 and then sets y = x = 3
int z = x--;  // Suffix or postfix increment first sets z = x = 3 and then x changes to 2
```

### Task
What will the following code output?
```cpp
#include
using namespace std;

int main()
{
    int a = 5;
    int b = 5;
    a--;
    cout << a;
    b = ++a;
    cout << b++;
    cout << b;

    return 0;
}
```

